"title": "5663: childbirth",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5663: childbirth",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Seen by Scripture as a token of God's favour, and used figuratively to picture a number of central biblical themes.</p>\n<h2>Childbirth in the OT</h2>\n<h3>Childbirth as a blessing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:28\">GEN 1:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:14\">DEU 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps127:3-Ps127:5\">PSA 127:3–127:5</a></p>\n<h3>Childlessness a cause of shame in Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:1\">GEN 30:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:6\">1SA 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:10-1Sam1:11\">1SA 1:10–1:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:24-Luke1:25\">LUK 1:24–1:25</a></p>\n<h2>The nature of human childbirth</h2>\n<h3>The pain of childbirth a consequence of the fall</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:16\">GEN 3:16</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The need for ceremonial purification after childbirth</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:1-Lev12:8\">LEV 12:1–12:8</a> <em>Under the old covenant, unsanctioned contact with blood was ceremonially defiling</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:24\">LUK 2:24</a></p>\n<h3>The role of midwives in childbirth</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:15-Exod1:21\">EXO 1:15–1:21</a></p>\n<h3>The joy of childbirth</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:6\">GEN 21:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:21\">JHN 16:21</a></p>\n<h2>Childbirth and salvation</h2>\n<h3>The birth of a Saviour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:15\">GEN 3:15</a></strong> <em>Although childbirth is a focus of judgment, through it the human race continues, and the Messiah comes into the world.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:2-Gen12:3\">GEN 12:2–12:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:3-Gen15:6\">GEN 15:3–15:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:14\">ISA 7:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:6-Isa9:7\">ISA 9:6–9:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:18-Matt1:25\">MAT 1:18–1:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:35\">LUK 1:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:4-Luke2:7\">LUK 2:4–2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:16\">GAL 3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4\">GAL 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:5\">REV 12:5</a></p>\n<h3>Salvation in childbearing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:15\">1TI 2:15</a></strong> <em>A Christian mother fulfils her calling in childbearing; some take it to mean she will be kept safe in childbirth. Some, however, take this verse as a reference to <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:15\">Ge 3:15</a>, and the coming of Jesus Christ, as above.</em></p>\n<h2>Childbirth used figuratively</h2>\n<h3>To describe weakness and vulnerability</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:4-Ezek16:6\">EZK 16:4–16:6</a></p>\n<h3>To describe weakness under judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:3\">2KI 19:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:3\">ISA 37:3</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps48:6\">PSA 48:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa23:4\">ISA 23:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:17-Isa26:18\">ISA 26:17–26:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:31\">JER 4:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:3\">HOS 2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos13:13\">HOS 13:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:10\">MIC 4:10</a></p>\n<h3>To describe troubles prior to God's final triumph</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:7-Matt24:8\">MAT 24:7–24:8</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:8\">MRK 13:8</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:22\">ROM 8:22</a></p>\n<h3>To describe love and compassion</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:15\">ISA 49:15</a></p>\n<h3>To describe regeneration</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:6-John3:7\">JHN 3:6–3:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12-John1:13\">JHN 1:12–1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:18\">JAS 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:23\">1PE 1:23</a></p>\n<h3>To describe pastoral concern</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:19\">GAL 4:19</a></p>\n<h3>To describe the disciples' joy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:21-John16:22\">JHN 16:21–16:22</a></p>\n<h3>To describe triumph and salvation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:1\">ISA 54:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:27\">GAL 4:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:19\">ISA 26:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:7-Isa66:11\">ISA 66:7–66:11</a></p>\n<h2>God's sovereignty in childbirth</h2>\n<h3>All children are God's gift</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps127:3\">PSA 127:3</a></p>\n<h3>God controls the events of childbirth</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:22-Gen25:23\">GEN 25:22–25:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:13\">PSA 139:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:16\">PSA 139:16</a></p>\n<h3>Childbirth in old age</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:16-Gen17:19\">GEN 17:16–17:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:5-Luke1:13\">LUK 1:5–1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:18-Luke1:20\">LUK 1:18–1:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:23-Luke1:25\">LUK 1:23–1:25</a></p>\n<h3>Childbirth as an answer to prayer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:21\">GEN 25:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:20\">1SA 1:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:13\">LUK 1:13</a></p>\n<h3>Childbirth for the barren woman</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps113:9\">PSA 113:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:21\">GEN 25:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:2-Judg13:5\">JDG 13:2–13:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:5\">1SA 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:1\">ISA 54:1</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ born of a virgin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:14\">ISA 7:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:22-Matt1:23\">MAT 1:22–1:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:18\">MAT 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:30-Luke1:31\">LUK 1:30–1:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:34-Luke1:37\">LUK 1:34–1:37</a> <em>“impossible” births demonstrate God's power and grace and show that salvation comes from the Lord.</em></p>",
